## Benchmark Results

Evaluated on 5 curated clinical vignettes (MDD, MI, Pneumonia, GAD, T2DM).
Each case has a clinically correct response and a plausible-but-flawed response.

| Case | Condition | Good â†‘ | Poor â†“ | Î” | Re-rank âœ“ |
|---|---|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|
| MDD_001 | Major Depressive Disorder | 0.92 | 0.28 | +0.64 | âœ… |
| MI_001 | Myocardial Infarction | 0.80 | 0.36 | +0.44 | âœ… |
| PNE_001 | Community-Acquired Pneumonia | 0.80 | 0.40 | +0.40 | âœ… |
| GAD_001 | Generalised Anxiety Disorder | 0.89 | 0.28 | +0.61 | âœ… |
| DM2_001 | Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus | 0.88 | 0.36 | +0.52 | âœ… |

**Re-ranking accuracy: 5/5 (100%) Â· Average score delta: +0.52**

> Re-ranking consistently selects the clinically correct response without any additional model training.

